  <info>
    <title>Creating volume groups</title>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="jsindelarova@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract>
      <para>
        This topic focuses on creating volume groups from several disks that
        can later be used to create, for example, a logical volume.
      </para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <para>
    To create a volume group of disks, proceed as follows:
  </para>
  <procedure>
    <step>
      <para>
        Click <guimenu>Storage</guimenu>.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Under the hamburger menu in <guimenu>Devices</guimenu>, select
        <guimenu>Create volume group</guimenu>.
      </para>
      <!--
        <figure xml:id="fig-volume-groups">
        <title>Creating a volume group</title>
        <mediaobject>
        <imageobject role="fo">
        <imagedata  fileref="cockpit_volume_groups.png" width="100%"/>
        </imageobject>
        <imageobject role="html">
        <imagedata fileref="cockpit_volume_groups.png" width="100%"/>
        </imageobject>
        <textobject role="description"><phrase>Volume group</phrase>
        </textobject>
        </mediaobject>
        </figure>
        -->
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Enter the volume group name.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Select disks that will be part of the volume group.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Confirm the data with <guimenu>Create</guimenu>. The volume group
        appears in the <guimenu>Devices</guimenu> view.
      </para>
    </step>
  </procedure>
</topic>
